Tried it out. It looks great, but as expected there are still a few bugs, etc.:

1. Did you know the .dll is not in the Plugins folder? Not sure if that's necessary, but because I at first thought I thought it didn't work I moved it to the Plugins folder. Turns out the problem was caused by something else. It does work if it's put in the Plugins folder.

2. The problem I encountered was that I launched an unmanned version. Once in space I opened the windows and then clicked on 'find the refit module' or whatever the other buttons called. When I got my manned craft to the wet workshop and put a Kerbil in the refit module, it wouldn't let me refit it. No button. When I launched another workshop I put a Kerbal in before I clicked 'find the refit module'. This time it worked as it should.

3. I had leftover equipment after completing the tank conversion. Made it a bit unclear whether or not I was done yet.

I may have found an issue, the Caterpillar Tracks mod may conflict with this mod.

I made four conversion attempts while I had tracks attached to the fuel tank. Two attempts where successful and two failures when the conversion button did not appear.

But in all four attempts the caterpillar tracks would not drive forward or backwards, they would only turn left or right.

Two conversion attempts without treads did work.
